ðŸ§­ Step-by-Step: Create a Search Index in Azure Portal
1. Provision an Azure AI Search Resource
- Go to https://portal.azure.com
- Click "Create a resource"
- Search for "Azure AI Search"
- Click Create, then fill out:
  - Subscription
  - Resource group
  - Name
  - Region
  - Pricing tier (start with Free for testing)
- Click Review + create, then Create

2. Open the Import Data Wizard
- Once the resource is deployed, go to your Azure AI Search resource
- Click Import data at the top of the Overview page

3. Choose a Data Source
- Select an existing Azure Storage account, SQL Database, or other source
- Provide necessary connection information and credentials
- Select the container, table, or collection where your data is stored

4. Define the Index
- The wizard analyzes your data and suggests field names and types
- You can customize:
  - Field names
  - Field data types (Edm.String, Edm.Double, etc.)
  - Attributes like searchable, filterable, sortable, facetable

5. Configure Indexer and AI Enrichment (Optional)
- Decide if you want to use AI enrichment (OCR, sentiment, language detection, etc.)
- Configure or skip adding a skillset
- Name and schedule your indexer (run once or on a schedule)

6. Review and Create
- Review all settings for Data Source, Index, Indexer, and optional Skillset
- Click Create

